  <title>Appendix - Array List Header Implementation</title>

  <p>The final implementation of ArrayList as a header file is shown below. Note that all the code for the ArrayList class is included in this file. There will not be an `ArrayList.cpp` file.</p>

  <p>Other than the lack of module/export definitions, and the inclusion of a header guard, the primary difference between the header version and module version is the lack of `using namespace std` in the header version. Whereas a module can use `using` without polluting the namespace of code that `imports` the module, a header file should avoid using `using` directives to prevent potential naming conflicts.</p>

